comments.message:
I think there's some serious confusion on how entity-manager config files work.  a "GPIO ipmb sensor" is not something that exists on the board, and therefore shouldn't have a direct config file.  The thing that exists in this case is the facebook twinlake controller, for which the configuration should look something like

{
"Type": "TwinlakeHostController"
"Bus": 1
}

considering that's everything that needs to be configurable for a specific instance, as all else is known from that device name.  ANy specific oem netfn, or command sets should be handled within code.

Are you planning to remove any error log from this method ?
I was suggesting something like below. It will print as many error as existing exception thing does.


void IpmbPowerMonitor::incrementError()
{
    if (retryCount >= 3)
    {
        retryCount = 0;
        std::cerr << "Error log" << "\n";
    }
    retryCount++;
}

I might be missing something, but I don't see how this code make it stop.
This function reset the retryCount when it exceed the limit, and read() is always called to schedule next after incrementError
